  "description": "Bird was first spotted by David Dowell out on ice. It was clearly paler and more petite than nearby Herring Gulls. Head appeared delicate and bill very small when c/w nearby HERG. Body size smaller than HERGs but definitely closer in size to HERGs than RBGUs. \u00a0Eye nearly white. feet pink. Bill mix of bright yellow and pallid yellow with orange-red gonydeal spot. Wing pattern clearly shown in photos, within range of Kumlien's ICGU but not THGU.",
